    bibo:volume "2246" ;
    dc:creator "Mecke, Sven; Doughty, Paul; Donnellan, Stephen C." ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Eremiascincus (Reptilia: Squamata: Scincidae) from the Great Sandy Desert and Pilbara Coast, Western Australia and reassignment of eight species from Glaphyromorphus to Eremiascincus" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190709>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190710>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190708>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190711> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190709>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Drawings of head and dorsal scalation of the digits of the pes (left side) of holotype of Eremiascincus musivus" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/190709/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190710>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Dorsum (A) and flank (B) of preserved holotype of Eremiascincus musivus sp. nov., (WAM R 165266). Total length = 138.2 mm. Photograph—R. Heitzmann." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/190710/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190708>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Map showing the distribution of E. fasciolatus (open triangles), E. isolepis (shaded circles), and E. musivus sp. nov. (solid squares) based on vouchered museum specimens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/190708/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190711>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Habitat of E. musivus sp. nov. 20 km ENE Karratha, Pilbara coast, northern Western Australia. Sloping dune with buffel grass vegetation on red siliceous sand. Both the holotype (WAM R 165266) and two paratypes (WAM R 165264 – 5) were collected from this site. Photograph—Biota Environmental Sciences Pty Ltd." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/190711/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

